com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-02T15:39:24Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-02T15:39:24Z\",\"body\":\"```\\r\\nKey Findings\\r\\n\\r\\nYes, it is possible. The 5 core expression forms of the Calculus of Constructions (variables, sorts, Π-types, λ-abstraction, application) map naturally to LiNo expressions.\\r\\n\\r\\nLinks Theory aligns with dependent type theory. Both systems unify \\\"terms\\\" and \\\"types\\\" into a single syntactic category — in CIC, a type is just a term; in Links Theory, everything is a link. This shared principle of self-reference makes LiNo a natural notation for type theory.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe probabilistic extension is the novel contribution. By combining ADL's many-valued logic with dependent types, we can create a system where propositions have degrees of truth (not just inhabited/empty), enabling Bayesian reasoning within a formal type-theoretic framework.\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nLet's do that, make sure tests are additive (keeping backward compatibility), let's implement types/dependent types to be meta theory for Lean/Rocq, through the idea that `in Links Theory, everything is a link`.\\r\\n\\r\\nImplement it in both JavaScript and Rust.\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3835961228/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3835966714\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3835966714\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3835966714,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kpDT6\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-02T15:40:09Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-02T15:40:09Z\",\"body\":\"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\\n\\nStarting automated work session at 2026-02-02T15:40:07.233Z\\n\\nThe PR has been converted to draft mode while work is in progress.\\n\\n_This comment marks the beginning of an AI work session. Please wait working session to finish, and provide your feedback._\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3835966714/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836046839\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3836046839\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3836046839,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kpW33\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-02T15:52:47Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-02T16:04:05Z\",\"body\":\"`':'` is not good in Links Notation syntax as expression in the middle, let's do instead of `x : Type` this: `x as Type`. Or `x has Type`, `x of Type`, where appropriate.\\r\\n\\r\\nOr we sometimes can have, something like: `(true: Boolean true)`, `(false: Boolean false)`, so that means we can also have type as prefix notation, as well as `(Boolean: Type Boolean)`.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs in \\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\nTree:\\r\\n\\r\\ntype\\r\\n └─ boolean\\r\\n      ├─ true\\r\\n      └─ false\\r\\nLinks Notation (indented syntax):\\r\\n\\r\\ntype\\r\\n  boolean\\r\\n    true\\r\\n    false\\r\\nLinks Notation (inline syntax):\\r\\n\\r\\n(type: type type)\\r\\n(boolean: type boolean)\\r\\n(true: boolean true)\\r\\n(false: boolean false)\\r\\nHint:\\r\\n\\r\\n(type: type subtype)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nBut note, that by default our true and false are defined as min/max of range, these are just possible redefinitions. And should serve as example/standard for general type hierarchy syntax.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso we can use more natural getters like: `(? (type of x))` or checks `(? (x is type))`.\\r\\n\\r\\nMake sure to update all tests in JavaScript and Rust, so `:` is used only for definition of links/links-aliases/links-variables/links-types and so on ... as we used it previously and in no other way.\\r\\n\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836046839/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836120564\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3836120564\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3836120564,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kpo30\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":