ion/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3836144580\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3836144580,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kpuvE\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-02T16:08:30Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-02T16:08:30Z\",\"body\":\"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\\n\\nStarting automated work session at 2026-02-02T16:08:28.368Z\\n\\nThe PR has been converted to draft mode while work is in progress.\\n\\n_This comment marks the beginning of an AI work session. Please wait working session to finish, and provide your feedback._\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836144580/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836177007\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3836177007\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3836177007,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kp2pv\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-02T16:12:52Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-02-02T16:24:28Z\",\"body\":\"```\\r\\n(? (x type-of Nat)), (?type x)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nInstead of this we should use:\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\n(? (x of Nat)), (? (type of x))\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nOr similar, so no `type-of` in any place.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso I don't like short names like `lam` or `app`, we should use full names where possible for new users to speed up understanding. `Pi` can be kept short. `id` is `identity function`? If yes, let's at least name it `identity`.\\r\\n\\r\\nMake sure we have README.md files in ./rust, and ./js folders, with language specific description, and common README.md in the root.\\r\\n\\r\\nAnd all features should be mentioned in docs, if README.md files grow too large, ensure we have sections for detailed description of all sections in `./docs` folder.\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\n# Colon notation (compact)\\r\\n(zero: Nat)\\r\\n\\r\\n# Prefix type notation (LiNo-native, aligns with link patterns)\\r\\n(zero: Nat zero)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nCompact notation will not work, because we will lose ability to set aliases in such way. Zero is not natural numbers set/type/category. So the only thing that should work between these two is `(zero: Nat zero)`. Because that is specific enough that is Nat zero, meaning zero instance of Nat.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn `lambda`'s we should use syntax like this: `(lambda (Natural x, Natural y) (x + 1)) `.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso we should never use `Nat`, only `Natural`.\",\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836177007/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"performed_via_github_app\":null},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/comments/3836244097\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/pull/14#issuecomment-3836244097\",\"issue_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/associative-dependent-logic/issues/14\",\"id\":3836244097,\"node_id\":\"IC_kwDOP9nMvc7kqHCB\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"konard\",\"id\":1431904,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/konard\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.c