ple, nested, deeply nested AST construction\n- Environment tests (lines 51-73) - operators, custom ops, expressions, probabilities\n- Evaluation tests (lines 75-100+) - literals, definitions, redefinitions, operators\n\n**Coverage includes:**\n- Tokenization, parsing, quantization\n- Evaluation logic and operator aggregators\n- Many-valued logics: unary, binary (Boolean), ternary (Kleene), quaternary, quinary, N-valued, continuous\n- Both `[0, 1]` and `[-1, 1]` ranges\n- Truth constants: defaults, redefinition, range changes, quantization with valence\n- Liar paradox resolution\n- Decimal-precision arithmetic\n- **Dependent type system:** universes, Pi-types, lambdas, application, type queries, prefix type notation\n\n#### Rust Tests\n**File:** `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1770051677391/rust/src/lib.rs` (embedded as module tests)\n\n**Coverage:** Identical 170 tests mirroring JavaScript test suite\n\n---\n\n### 4. README Documentation\n\n**Root README:**\n- **Path:** `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1770051677391/README.md`\n- **Content:** Project overview, supported logic types, quick start, syntax guide, examples, testing info\n\n**JavaScript README:**\n- **Path:** `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1770051677391/js/README.md`\n- **Content:** Prerequisites, installation, usage, API documentation, testing, dependencies\n\n**Rust README:**\n- **Path:** `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1770051677391/rust/README.md`\n- **Content:** Prerequisites, building, usage, API documentation, testing, implementation notes\n\n**Architecture Documentation:**\n- **Path:** `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1770051677391/ARCHITECTURE.md`\n- **Content:** Project structure, processing pipeline, environment design, operators, decimal-precision arithmetic, key design decisions, testing organization\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Implementation Details\n\n#### Type System Notation\nBoth implementations support:\n1. **Colon form:** `(x: A)` - standard LiNo link definition\n2. **Prefix type form:** `(A x)` - type-first notation for lambdas/Pi bindings\n